akas: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (original title)
akas from release info: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (original title)

1.title: Fish Out of Water

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

1.plot: The prodigies will have to sink or swim when they face off against Executive Chef Drew Tsang, who takes them to task in three rounds that all revolve around seafood. Who's ready for some mouth-watering alligator picatta? Master Chef Jen Carroll presents and judges our third and final winner-takes-all round.

2.title: Decadent Delights

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

2.plot: It's Executive Chef Zoe Schor's turn to shore up the competition against the prodigies. With a theme like "Guilty pleasures" every round is sure to be absolutely delicious. But will our prodigies conquer with caviar? Or will Chef Schor shut them down with her Deadly Sin-inspired trio? Master Chef Antonia Lofaso presents and judges our third and final winner-takes-all round.

3.title: Danger Zone

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

3.plot: Executive Chef Johnny "Danger" Zone enters the Man vs. Child kitchen to take on our mini-masters. "Comfort Food" may be the theme, but this culinary showdown will be anything but "comfortable". Will the prodigies be able to take down the professional with a grilled cheese trio that can wow Chef Eric Greenspan, the "God of Grilled Cheese" in the final, winner-takes-all round?

4.title: Mardi Gras

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

4.plot: Executive Chef Sevan Abdessian has no intention of being defeated in the kitchen by a team of children. Exploding into the Man vs. Child kitchen, Chef Sevan breaks out the big flavors in New Orleans-inspired challenges, from po' boys to crawfish. Can our fantastic five bring the heat, fun and flavor of Mardi Gras and come out with a win? 'Nawlins native Marcus Christiana-Beninger presents and judges the third and final winner-takes-all round.

5.title: The Mamas and the Tapas

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

5.plot: The child cooking prodigies take on Executive Chef Dustin Trani in three rounds of competition, loaded with Spanish flair. It will all come down to who's tapas are perfecto, in the eyes of Master Chef Perfecto Rocher.

6.title: Keep Calm and Curry On

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

6.plot: Chicago's Bib Gourmand darling, Executive Chef Jill Barron, takes on the child cooking prodigies in three rounds of Indian food inspired challenges. Right at the start, things get nuts as the prodigies work hard to top Jill's impeccable technique and flavor profiles. But can they curry favor with the judges for the win? Master Chef Maneet Chouhan presents and judges the winner takes all round.

7.title: Work of Art

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

7.plot: Armed with his steam punk goggles, Executive Chef Richie Farina brings his creative flair to the Man Vs. Child kitchen. From palette to palate, tonight's challenges are frame worthy celebrations of food as artistic expression. It's childlike imagination vs. Chef Richie's avant guard techniques. Who will ultimately triumph? Two Michelin star Master Chef, Dominque Crenn, presents and judges the final, winner takes all round.

8.title: Feast from the East

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

8.plot: Executive Chef Jason Febres enters the Man vs. Child kitchen ready to take down the prodigies. Tonight's theme is all about Asian cuisine and with his expert fusion flavors, Chef Jason is not going go easy on our mini masters. Can the prodigies ultimately out bold Chef Jason's out of the box dishes? Tao Group's Corporate Chef and Partner Ralph Scamardella presents and judges the final, trios round.

9.title: Toast of the Town

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

9.plot: The prodigies take on Cali cool Executive Chef, Chris "Malibu" Crary in three rounds of competition. From a "toast" challenge in round one, to a "small fish" entree in round two and finally a "pickled and fermented trio," this episode is a foodie's dream. But while the prodigies may be hip to the latest trends, will it be enough to out cook the competition? LA's most sought after cooking duo, Master Chefs, Jon Shook and Vinny Dotolo present and judge the final round.

10.title: America the Beautiful

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

10.plot: Chef Melvin "Boots" Johnson takes on the child prodigies with American pride. In the first two rounds, they tackle classics such as hot dogs and pie. In the third and final round, Master Chef Bruce Kalman judges another American favorite--a trio of pizzas.

11.title: Roman Holiday

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

11.plot: America's favorite cooking prodigies take on Austin's up and coming Executive Chef, Roman Murphy in three rounds of competition. From prickly pears to burritos, tonight is all about the trendy foods of the Southwest. San Antonio's Tex Mex king, Master Chef Johnny Hernandez judges the final round.

12.title: Where There's Smoke...

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

12.plot: Things go south in the Man vs. Child kitchen, as the child cooking prodigies take on New York's Kelvin Fernandez in three delicious southern comfort themed challenges. Who'll bring home the bacon? Legendary Master Chef Jonathan Waxman judges the final round.

13.title: Cake Walk

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

13.plot: Toss your saltshakers aside because tonight, Man vs. Child is diving into the sweet world of baking! She may not be a pastry chef, but Executive Chef Bev Lazo is bringing her years of experience to out "whip" the competition. LA's premiere chocolatier, Master Chef Valerie Gordon judges the final round.

14.title: A Chef's Life

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

14.plot: Executive Chef Crystal "Pink" Delongpre brings her years of experience and culinary themed tattoos to the Man vs. Child competition. Tonight's challenges celebrate the techniques that separate the home cooks from the pros. But can our team of mini masters take on a chef of Pink's caliber? Master Chef Bruce Bromberg judges the final round.

15.title: It's a Family Affair

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

15.plot: Executive Chef Susie Jimenez spices up the Man vs. Child kitchen with her competitive edge and sassy attitude. From a one-pot wonder to secret family recipes, tonight's challenges celebrate the foods we learned to cook at home. Master Chef Betty Fraser judges the final round.

16.title: Back to School

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

16.plot: School's in session! Executive Chef Larry Keck battles the team of child cooking prodigies in three rounds of back to school themed challenges. But is team prodigy's knowledge of cookies and school lunches enough to take on Larry's 40 years of experience? England's youngest Master Chef, Luke Thomas judges the final round.

17.title: The Emperor Has No Stove

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

17.plot: Cooking competition veteran and Hollywood's rising star Executive Chef Mette Williams is here to battle the team of child cooking prodigies. From potatoes to Renaissance aged foods, tonight's theme is a culinary blast from the past. Master Chef extraordinaire, Susan Feniger judges the final round.

18.title: Home Cooking

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

18.plot: Tonight's season finale has all the fixings for a delicious competition. Highly notable Executive Chef Eli Kirshstein battles the team of child cooking prodigies in three rounds of home cooking themed challenges. Master Chef Art Smith brings down the house as he judges the final round.

1.title: Don't Under-ESTIE-Mate Her

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

1.plot: Executive Chef Frank Otte tests his mettle against a team of five child cooking prodigies; from "finger foods" to a "technique trio," can this acclaimed executive chef hold his own against 7-year old child chef Estie?

2.title: Stop the Bull!

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

2.plot: Frankie "The Bull" Terzoli does his best to stomp out the team of child cooking prodigies winning streak. When chef Emmalee is stymied by the perils of the menu board in the winner-takes all third round, will she "get the horns" or fight her way out? Founder of the "fo-nut" and celebrity pastry chef, Waylyn Lucas, joins to blind taste and judge the winner takes all final round.

3.title: All's Fair in Love and... Food?

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

3.plot: Chef Tony learns the hard way that small can be very mighty as he takes on the team of child cooking prodigies in tonight's "fair-food episode". Master Chef Brooke Williamson joins to blind taste and judge the winner takes all final round.

4.title: How Eggs-Centric

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

4.plot: Chef Katherine Humphus takes on the team of child cooking prodigies in this egg-centric episode - which revolves around a perennial favorite - eggs! World-famous celebrity chef, Hubert Keller, joins to blind taste and judge the winner takes all final round.

5.title: Secret Garden

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

5.plot: Executive chef Joel Miller is in the hot seat, placing his years of training and decades of experience on the line against the team of child cooking prodigies.

6.title: Viva La France

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

6.plot: Culinary and literal giant, chef Keith Breedlove muscles his way into the kitchen to see what all the fuss is about. But when he squares off against 7 year-old chef Estie in the "Poulet-Trois" will he crow like the rooster? Or run away chicken? Legendary Master Chef, Ludo Lefebvre, joins to blind taste and judge the winner takes all final round.

7.title: South of the Border

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

7.plot: Chef Diana Stavaridis tests the team of child cooking prodigies in a Mexican standoff! From Ceviche to taco-trios, if you can't take the heat, you'll get thrown out of the kitchen! The round three special guest judge is known for single-handedly revitalizing Tijuana's food scene, master chef Javier Plascencia.

8.title: Game-ON!

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

8.plot: Executive chef, Chris Tzorin, wants a piece of the action and competes against the team of child cooking prodigies. A culinary mash-up appetizer will test everyone's culinary creativity. Then it's going to be a knife fight, testing both sides in butchery skills - from making fresh sausage, to handling oversized cuts of game meat. Master Chef Karen Hatsfield joins to blind taste and judge the winner takes all final round.

9.title: In for a Penny, in for a Pound

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

9.plot: Executive chef Penny Davidi steps up to the team of child cooking prodigies wearing a sleeveless chef coat more reminiscent of a karate gi, than a coat. And don't be fooled, it's not a style choice, it's a warning! From the start, she'll spit venom at the mini-masters to put them off their game. Will the prodigies cave to fear? Or will they make Penny "eat her words". Master Chef and restaurateur, Jeff Mahin, joins to blind taste and judge the winner takes all final round.

10.title: Tough Luck

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

10.plot: Chef Larry Monaco may be the toughest match yet for the team of child cooking prodigies. From an "amuse" challenge in round one, out to a "tough cuts only" entree in round two and finally a "funghi" trio, this episode couldn't be any more foodie! Two-time Michelin star-rated Master Chef, Josia Citrin, joins to blind taste and judge the winner takes all final round.

11.title: It Takes Guts!

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

11.plot: Chef Augie Saucido wants to see what all the fuss is about as he competes against the team of child cooking prodigies. And, from the moment he steps in, it gets raw! Raw food preparation is on the menu in round one.

12.title: Wild Enough to Be Shot At...

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

12.plot: Chef Hop Fan crashes into the kitchen with his eclectic mix of "Ed Grimley" meets "Kramer" antics - is he a creative genius or a madman? Can the team of child cooking prodigies stay focused and take this chef down? From a sushi challenge to a street food trio, be prepared for amazing food and some kitchen comedy! Master Chef, Mary Sue Milliken, joins to blind taste and judge the winner takes all final round.

13.title: Awww Shucks!

episode of.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown (TV Series 2015– )

13.plot: It's executive chef Justin Haefler's chance to put his years of training and decades of experience on the line for a chance to beat the team of child cooking prodigies in the kitchen! Live oyster appetizers will test their shucking skills.

imdb.title: Man vs. Child: Chef Showdown
plot: Each week, a team of five child cooking prodigies, ages 9 through 16, challenges an executive-level chef in the kitchen, in a three-round competition.::Mike
